Remove dependence on telnetlib which was removed from Python 3.13 (#626)

commit.message: Fix co_lines test for Py 3.10 and 3.11
Use co_lines to find executable lines if available
Try to bring syntax highlighting more in line with nord themes seen elsewhere
Define all 16 colours of the nord theme
Add a bold highlight to sidebar header when focused
Use regular source background for warnings
Give each theme its own file
Delay letting '_have_debugger' return True until Debugger is fully initialized
Scroll cmdline results on shift page up/down

Always recall the just executed command on arrow up

After executing a command, immediatly hitting the arrow up key should
recall the just executed command again, like in all shells.
This commit ensures this behavior by clearing out the saved edit text on
successful command execution.

Previously, it recalled the last saved edit text if set, which is an
annoying workflow break compared to other shells.
